comments: He is the best teacher I\'ve ever had at UMich. Join his band if you can- you won\'t regret it. He is super understanding and trusts his students.

Professor Haithcock is an OK conductor. He\'s nothing to write home about, but he\'s not terrible. He\'s definitely overrated. As a person, he is extremely stuck up. He has way too big of an ego. He\'s mediocre at best.

Professor Haithcock is the single most influential professor in my educational career. His rehearsals are the highlight of my semester. I and any of my colleagues would do anything for him - inspirational, ridiculously clear about his expectations, TRUSTING of his students, extremely knowledgeable, engaging, and funny. This man is on your side.
